{
  "stem": "27335.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She just came, and we looked at each other, you know we stopped and just looked and stared at each other.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you, and you-- [LAUGHS] and that-- that was the last time I-- I met her.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She married already.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But she was a handsome-looking girl.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, well, in the public school-- in the village, in the public school, uh, every one of the Jewish kids went to the Protestant church, because the Catholic church didn't a-a-accept them.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But they used to have-- used to have the Hebrew classes at the weekend, they're usually on Sundays, at-- at the synagogue there, and the-- and the rabbi's house there.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that was the schoolhouse where they have the, uh-- well, even that-- you see, I never-- never heard, in like Yiddish, I never heard a word until I came to Canada.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Hebrew, I heard it because I mixed with the kids there, and one time, I remember, I just sneaked in, sits down in there, on the bench there, and just listened to Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And somehow it fascinated me, and so--",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, well, not so much, but they-- they did the teacher, you see, and they taught them Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "N-n-not very many, mind you, because it was so assimilated that the-- the Jewish, the Jewish population-- I hardly heard any-- any-- any Hebrew talks among the Jews.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were all Hungarians.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "More Hungarian then the Hungarians-- I'm not kidding that-- [LAUGHS] that that's how they lived-- lived in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I think it was sort of a planned way in their part to assimilate, and then be able to-- to-- to avoid persecution, and some pogroms.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, uh, and so it happened.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And up till the day of Hitler came.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Thank you.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
